      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, you can protect yourself by choosing an ARM with specific adjustment caps, which limit how much your rate can change at once or over the life of the loan. Standard ARMs typically have an annual cap (solitary cap) around 2% and a lifetime cap at 5% to 6% above your starting rate, preventing drastic jumps even in volatile markets. Additionally, some lenders structure these caps so that if rates rise due to an economic downturn, they can be capped only by a specific percentage, such as 5%, providing stability, rather than allowing infinite fluctuation. Choosing a loan with these built-in limits ensures that while you might pay more than the initial rate, your escalations remain within predictable boundaries compared to non-capped options.",
